               <head>Treatise on Sufism and pantheism</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of a work by ʿAbd al-ʿAlī ibn Niẓām al-Dīn al-Anṣārī</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008112367 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2006003807" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1025-item1">
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164656951.0x000001 viaf_26942027">ʿAbd al-ʿAlī ibn Niẓām al-Dīn al-Anṣārī</persName>
                     </author>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Untitled Persian treatise on Sufism and concepts of pantheism, based on the Arabic original by the same author, <persName key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164656951.0x000001 viaf_26942027" role="aut">ʿAbd al-ʿAlī ibn Niẓām al-Dīn al-Anṣārī</persName> (d. 1235/1820). 
                        </p>
                        <p>The work was written at the order of the patron, <persName key="viaf_24160324" role="pat">Amīr Vālājāh Bahādur</persName> (added in margin, <persName key="viaf_24160324" role="pat">Muḥammad ʿAlī Khān) ibn Anvār al-Dīn Khān Bahādur</persName> (d. 1795), the second <persName key="viaf_24160324" role="pat">Navvāb of Arkāt/Arcot</persName>, ruler of the Carnatic. 
                        </p>
                        <p>The work begins with an Arabic preface. 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                        <p>Illuminated ʿunvān folio 1v; gilded ruled borders. 
</p>
                     </note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
